# ERP Party Master Standard

## Customer Functionality

All customer functionality MUST use the Unified Party Master.

**Active customer route:**
```
/admin/master-data/parties/customers
```

**Do NOT use or reference:**
```
/admin/master-data/customers         ← legacy, redirects to party master
/admin/master-data/customers/record/ ← legacy, redirects to party master
```

## Rules

1. Customer records are Party records with `CUSTOMER` party type.
2. Add Customer = Add Party via `/admin/master-data/parties/record/new`.
3. View/Edit Customer = open Party record from the Customers filtered view.
4. Customer contacts, addresses, bank details = Party child tabs.
5. Do NOT import or build against legacy customer feature files — they have been deleted.
6. Do NOT create new server actions against `customers`, `customer_contacts`, `customer_addresses`, `customer_bank_details`, or `customer_documents` tables — they have been dropped.
7. `customer_categories` and `customer_statuses` tables are RETAINED — they are used by `party_customer_profiles` (Party Master). Do not drop them.

## Workspace Route Registry

Legacy customer entries (`CUSTOMERS_LEGACY`) have been removed from `src/lib/workspace/workspace-route-registry.ts`.

The active party customer list tab is registered as:
```
/admin/master-data/parties/customers  (moduleCode: PARTY_MASTER)
```

